The paper analyzes the scientific output of Italian professors in the sciences, which suggests a focus on computer science (cs) as a whole. The aspect of research diversification is measured along three main dimensions, which could fall under several sub-categories. However, the use of regression models and the focus on cognitive relatedness of fields suggests a focus on topics related to data analysis (cs.DL), social networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), system and control (cs.SD), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
